INSERT INTO `question` VALUES (76,'B','EASY','Wood, Air, Spark','Fuel, Oxygen, Heat','Gas, Smoke, Light','Paper, Heat, Wind','What are the three elements of the fire triangle that a fire needs to keep burning?',1),(77,'C','EASY','100','102','101','108','What is the fire emergency number to call in India?',1),(78,'B','EASY','The lift for speed','The stairs','The window closest to you','The main entrance only','During a fire evacuation, which exit should you ALWAYS use?',1),(79,'C','EASY','Push','Point','Pull','Press','What does the letter P in the word PASS stand for when using a fire extinguisher?',1),(80,'B','EASY','Run to find water immediately','Stop, Drop and Roll','Take your clothes off and run','Jump into the nearest pool','What is the correct action if your clothes catch fire?',1),(81,'C','EASY','CO2 carbon dioxide extinguisher','Dry powder extinguisher','Red water extinguisher','Foam extinguisher','Which type of fire extinguisher must you NEVER use on an electrical fire?',1),(82,'C','EASY','Run fast through the smoke and hold your breath','Walk upright and cover your mouth with a cloth','Get low and crawl under the smoke','Open all windows before moving','If there is heavy smoke in a corridor during a fire, what should you do to breathe safely?',1),(83,'D','EASY','1 minute','3 minutes','5 minutes','At least 10 minutes','How long should you apply cool running water to a burn?',1),(84,'C','EASY','Open it quickly and run through before it gets worse','Pour water on the door to cool it first','Do not open it ΓÇö find another exit','Kick it open from a safe distance','If a door feels hot when you touch it during a fire, what should you do?',1),(85,'C','EASY','The school cafeteria or canteen','Any classroom on the ground floor','A designated safe open area away from the building','The principal or headmaster\'s office','What is the assembly point after a fire evacuation?',1),(86,'B','MEDIUM','Water damages electrical equipment beyond repair','Water conducts electricity and can electrocute the user','Water makes the electrical fire spread faster','Water extinguishers are too heavy to carry quickly','Why must you NEVER use a water extinguisher on an electrical fire?',1),(87,'C','MEDIUM','Red water extinguisher','CO2 carbon dioxide extinguisher','Dry powder or foam extinguisher','Sand only ΓÇö no extinguisher is right','A small fire starts in the chemistry lab from a burning liquid chemical. Which extinguisher is most appropriate?',1),(88,'B','MEDIUM','Try to extinguish it yourself, then call for help if it grows','Alert everyone and start evacuation immediately ΓÇö do not fight a growing fire','Call the fire brigade, then wait for them before doing anything else','Close all doors and windows to contain it, then alert people','You discover a fire in a classroom. It is growing fast. What is the correct priority order?',1),(89,'B','MEDIUM','The top is stronger and easier to push','Heat and hot gases collect at the top first, so the top tells you the danger sooner','It is simply a traditional habit from old fire training','The door handle is usually at the top in older buildings','Why should you touch a door at the TOP rather than the middle when checking if it is safe to open?',1),(90,'C','MEDIUM','Apply butter or coconut oil to soothe the burn','Wrap the burn tightly with fabric to protect it','Cover the burn loosely with a clean cloth and get them to medical help fast','Leave the burn open to air and wait for it to heal','After someone else\'s clothing fire is out, you have no cool water nearby. What should you do immediately?',1),(91,'B','MEDIUM','Using mobile phones near lab equipment','Overloading power sockets with too many devices','Running too many computers at the same time','Keeping lab lights on overnight','Which common school activity most commonly causes electrical fires in labs?',1),(92,'B','MEDIUM','Go back in quickly with them to help find it faster','Tell them it is not worth it and firmly stop them from re-entering','Let them decide for themselves ΓÇö it is their choice','Report it to a teacher when convenient','You are evacuating and see a classmate trying to go back inside to retrieve their backpack. What do you do?',1),(93,'C','MEDIUM','Aim at the highest visible flame','Aim at the smoke rising above the fire','Sweep side to side at the BASE of the fire','Spray in a circular motion around the fire','What is the correct S step in PASS ΓÇö where exactly do you aim the extinguisher?',1),(94,'B','MEDIUM','It removes fuel by smothering the material','It removes oxygen by displacing it with CO2 gas','It removes heat by cooling the fire rapidly','It removes all three simultaneously','Removing which element from the fire triangle does a CO2 extinguisher primarily achieve?',1),(95,'C','MEDIUM','Trust the teacher ΓÇö they know the building','Use your own judgement and enter if it looks safe from outside','Wait for the firefighter to officially clear the building ΓÇö their word overrides all others','Ask other students and decide by vote','After a fire evacuation, a teacher says you can go back in. A firefighter has NOT cleared the building yet. What do you do?',1),(96,'B','HARD','Use the lift since it is the fastest way out','Use the fire escape ladder ΓÇö it is a designated fire exit and lifts must never be used in fires','Stay on the 4th floor and wait ΓÇö smoke is less dangerous than height','Go to the rooftop and wait for helicopter rescue','You are on the 4th floor. All stairwells are reported to have smoke. There is a fire escape ladder accessible from the corridor window. The lift is functioning. What should you do?',1),(97,'B','HARD','Open the door quickly and run through before smoke fills the room','Seal gaps under the door with clothing, signal rescuers from the window, breathe low, wait for rescue','Break the window and jump regardless of the height to escape the fire','Lie on the floor in the centre of the room and wait','You are trapped in a room. The door is very hot. There are no other exits. What is the correct sequence of survival actions?',1),(98,'B','HARD','Use both together for maximum coverage ΓÇö more is always better','Use only the CO2 extinguisher ΓÇö water must never be used on electrical fires as it causes electrocution risk','Use the water extinguisher first to cool the area, then CO2','Use neither and immediately evacuate without attempting to fight it at all','An electrical fire starts in the server room. A red water extinguisher is closer but a CO2 extinguisher is further away. Someone says to use both for maximum effect. What is the correct decision?',1),(99,'C','HARD','Apply an antiseptic cream to prevent infection','Burst the large blisters carefully to release fluid before wrapping','Cover loosely with a clean sterile cloth and get immediate medical attention','Continue cooling with ice for another 10 minutes to reduce swelling','You help someone whose clothing caught fire. The fire is out. The burn looks deep, blistered, and covers a large area. After 10 minutes of cool water, what is the single most important next step?',1),(100,'B','HARD','Dry powder extinguishers are not effective on gas fires at all','Dry powder is effective on gas fires but creates a thick cloud that reduces visibility and can cause breathing issues in enclosed spaces','There is no trade-off ΓÇö dry powder is always the safest option for any fire','Dry powder only works outdoors and should not be used inside buildings','A student uses a dry powder extinguisher correctly on a small gas fire in a lab. The fire is out. The teacher notices the area is becoming dangerous due to the powder cloud reducing visibility. What was the trade-off of using dry powder here?',1),(101,'B','EASY','Critical Patient Response','Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation','Cardiac Pressure Revival','Chest and Pulse Recovery','What does CPR stand for?',14),(102,'D','EASY','100','101','102','108','What is the ambulance emergency number in India?',14),(103,'C','EASY','After 30 minutes','After 15 minutes','Within 4 to 6 minutes','After 1 hour','How soon do brain cells begin to die after the heart stops?',14),(104,'B','EASY','On the left side of the chest over the heart','On the centre of the chest on the lower half of the breastbone','On the upper chest near the collarbone','On the stomach below the ribs','Where do you place your hands for adult chest compressions?',14),(105,'C','EASY','1 centimetre','2 centimetres','At least 5 centimetres','10 centimetres','How deep should adult chest compressions be?',14),(106,'B','EASY','15 compressions to 1 breath','30 compressions to 2 breaths','20 compressions to 2 breaths','50 compressions to 1 breath','What is the correct compression to breath ratio for adult CPR?',14),(107,'B','EASY','Whether the person is insured','Whether the scene is safe for you to approach','Whether you have gloves available','Whether other people are watching','What should you check before approaching someone who may need CPR?',14),(108,'C','EASY','CPR using only one hand for compressions','CPR using gloved hands only','Continuous chest compressions without rescue breaths','A type of CPR only doctors can perform','What is hands-only CPR?',14),(109,'C','EASY','Full hand','One finger','Two fingers','Three fingers','How many fingers are used for chest compressions on an infant under 1 year old?',14),(110,'A','EASY','Automated External Defibrillator','Advanced Emergency Device','Automated Electric Dropper','Airway Emergency Device','What does AED stand for?',14),(111,'C','MEDIUM','60 to 80 compressions per minute','80 to 100 compressions per minute','100 to 120 compressions per minute','140 to 160 compressions per minute','What is the correct compression rate per minute for adult CPR?',14),(112,'B','MEDIUM','It prevents the rescuer from getting tired','It allows blood to refill the heart between compressions','It keeps the airway open for rescue breaths','It prevents ribs from breaking during CPR','Why is chest recoil important between compressions?',14),(113,'B','MEDIUM','Start CPR immediately, then call 108 when done','Call 108 first on speaker or get someone to call, then start CPR immediately','Wait for someone else to arrive before touching the person','Give rescue breaths first, then call 108, then start compressions','You are alone. You find an unconscious person who is not breathing. What is the correct order of actions?',14),(114,'B','MEDIUM','Press down on the forehead and push the chin down','Tilt the head back and lift the chin upward','Turn the head to one side and open the mouth','Push the jaw forward without touching the head','How do you open the airway before giving rescue breaths?',14),(115,'B','MEDIUM','A very quick puff of under half a second','About 1 second while watching the chest rise','At least 3 full seconds','As long as it takes to fill the lungs completely','How long should each rescue breath last when being given?',14),(116,'B','MEDIUM','The ratio changes to 50 compressions to 1 breath','You use one hand or two fingers for compressions and start with 5 initial rescue breaths','You do not give rescue breaths at all for children','Compression depth increases to 10 centimetres for children','For children aged 1 to puberty, what is different about CPR compared to adult CPR?',14),(117,'B','MEDIUM','No ΓÇö if there is any pulse at all, never do CPR','Yes ΓÇö if they are unresponsive and not breathing normally, start CPR even if unsure about pulse','No ΓÇö wait for their pulse to stop completely before starting','Only start CPR if the pulse disappears within 2 minutes','Someone collapses in your school corridor. A classmate says they have a weak pulse. Should you start CPR?',14),(118,'C','MEDIUM','Happy Birthday','We Will Rock You','Stayin Alive by the Bee Gees','Twinkle Twinkle Little Star','What song is commonly used to remember the correct CPR compression rate?',14),(119,'C','MEDIUM','30 to 2','20 to 2','15 to 2','10 to 1','When two rescuers are present for an infant, what compression to breath ratio should be used?',14),(120,'B','MEDIUM','Finish your current cycle of CPR then put the AED away','Use the AED as soon as possible ΓÇö it will give voice instructions','Only use AED if CPR has failed for more than 10 minutes','Let only a doctor use the AED ΓÇö continue CPR yourself','An AED becomes available while you are doing CPR. What should you do?',14),(121,'B','HARD','You are pressing in the wrong place ΓÇö stop CPR immediately','A rib may have cracked ΓÇö this can happen during correct CPR, continue compressions as broken ribs are better than death','CPR is working ΓÇö cracks mean the heart is restarting','You are pressing too fast ΓÇö slow down to 60 compressions per minute','You are giving CPR and hear a cracking sound from the chest. What does this most likely mean and what should you do?',14),(122,'B','HARD','No difference ΓÇö standard 30 to 2 ratio starting with compressions','Start with 5 initial rescue breaths before beginning compressions since drowning causes oxygen deprivation first','Only give compressions ΓÇö never give rescue breaths to a drowning victim','Do not do CPR on drowning victims as water in lungs makes it dangerous','A person was rescued from drowning and is unconscious and not breathing. How does CPR differ from standard cardiac arrest CPR?',14),(123,'C','HARD','Continue alone ΓÇö untrained people make CPR worse','Stop CPR and rest ΓÇö 8 minutes was enough','Guide the bystander through hands-only CPR with verbal instructions while you rest briefly, then switch','Ask the bystander to call 108 and stop CPR to preserve your energy','You have been doing CPR alone for 8 minutes and are exhausted. A bystander offers to help but says they do not know CPR. What should you do?',14),(124,'B','HARD','Immediately restart CPR ΓÇö they are confused and need more','Stop CPR, place them in the recovery position on their side, monitor breathing, and keep 108 on the way','Hold them down and continue CPR until the ambulance arrives','Give 5 more rescue breaths then stop','A person regains consciousness during CPR and pushes you away saying they are fine. What should you do?',14),(125,'C','HARD','Bystander CPR is illegal without medical certification in India','Bystander CPR is only useful if the person is under 40 years old','Bystander CPR can double or triple survival chances and any attempt is better than no attempt','Bystander CPR is only effective if started within 30 seconds of collapse','Which statement about bystander CPR is most accurate?',14),(151,'A','EASY','Hands clutching the throat','Person falls to the ground','Person starts sweating heavily','Person turns very pale','What is the first sign to look for when someone is choking?',18),(152,'B','EASY','The person is feeling cold','The brain is not receiving enough oxygen','The person is having an allergic reaction','Normal breathing is still occurring','What does a blue tint to the lips indicate during choking?',18),(153,'D','EASY','Call an ambulance and wait','Immediately perform back blows','Give them a glass of water','Encourage them to keep coughing','If a person can cough forcefully what should you do?',18),(154,'C','EASY','On the lower back','On the chest','Between the shoulder blades','On the neck','Where do you deliver back blows on a choking person?',18),(155,'D','EASY','Two','Ten','One','Five','How many back blows should you give before checking if the blockage cleared?',18),(156,'C','EASY','Back blows','Chest compressions','Abdominal thrusts','Rescue breathing','What is the Heimlich maneuver also called?',18),(157,'B','EASY','On the chest above the heart','Just above the navel below the breastbone','On the lower stomach near the hips','On the upper back','Where exactly is your fist placed for abdominal thrusts?',18),(158,'D','MEDIUM','Place them in recovery position and wait','Give only rescue breaths with no compressions','Continue abdominal thrusts only','Begin CPR and call emergency services','What should you do if the choking person becomes unconscious?',18),(159,'B','MEDIUM','Ten back blows continuously','Five back blows then five abdominal thrusts alternating','Back blows only until the object clears','Abdominal thrusts only with no back blows','What is the correct sequence when coughing fails to clear a choking obstruction?',18),(160,'D','MEDIUM','Lay the person down and pat gently','Use both hands simultaneously on the back','Keep the person upright and use your fist','Lean the person forward and use the heel of the hand firmly','How do you perform back blows correctly?',18),(161,'C','MEDIUM','Straight inward only','Downward and inward','Inward and upward in a J-shape','Outward and upward','What is the direction of the abdominal thrust motion?',18),(162,'C','MEDIUM','It is the only legally permitted method','It clears the entire airway instantly every time','It generates more pressure than any manual technique','External intervention is never permitted','Why is a strong natural cough more effective than external intervention?',18),(163,'D','MEDIUM','No modification is needed','Back blows only with no thrusts at all','Lay her flat and perform chest compressions','Chest thrusts instead of abdominal thrusts','What special modification is needed for a pregnant choking victim?',18),(164,'B','MEDIUM','Full Heimlich maneuver same as for adults','Five back blows then five chest thrusts using two fingers','Call an ambulance and do nothing else','Only back blows and nothing else','What should you do for a choking infant under one year old?',18),(165,'C','MEDIUM','Call emergency services and wait','Lie on the floor and try to relax','Thrust your abdomen against the back of a chair or hard edge','Drink water quickly to wash it down','If you are alone and choking what can you do?',18),(166,'D','HARD','The stomach muscles','The heart muscle','The lung walls','The diaphragm','Which muscle does the Heimlich maneuver primarily use to create expulsive pressure?',18),(167,'B','HARD','Only seek care if the person was unconscious','Medical evaluation as internal injury may have occurred','No follow-up is required if the person recovers fully','Only children need follow-up evaluation','After successfully removing a choking obstruction what follow-up is recommended?',18),(168,'C','HARD','No risk if performed with correct technique','Risk of breaking the spine','Internal injury to organs or ribs','Risk of pushing the object deeper','What risk does a forcefully performed Heimlich maneuver carry?',18),(169,'D','HARD','Water causes the throat tissue to swell','Water makes cyanosis worse rapidly','Water prevents abdominal thrusts from working','Swallowing can push the object deeper into the airway','Why should you never give a choking person water to drink?',18),(170,'C','HARD','Only after all manual techniques have completely failed','Only if the person loses consciousness','As soon as effective coughing stops and the person cannot breathe normally','After five full rounds of back blows and thrusts','At what point should you call emergency services during a choking incident?',18),(171,'B','HARD','Redness of the face from forceful coughing','Blue discolouration of skin from oxygen deprivation','Swelling of the throat tissue','Loss of consciousness from lack of oxygen','What is cyanosis in the context of choking?',18),(172,'D','HARD','Lower back with both hands','Sides of the ribcage','Upper stomach area','Chest at the same position as CPR compressions','For an obese person you cannot wrap your arms around where do you perform thrusts?',18),(173,'D','HARD','The obstruction has cleared successfully','The person is beginning to recover','The person is not actually choking','Complete or near-complete airway obstruction requiring immediate action','What does a silent cough indicate in a choking victim?',18),(174,'C','HARD','It directly pushes the object up the throat','It increases blood pressure around the blockage','It compresses the diaphragm upward increasing lung pressure to force air out','It massages the object loose from the throat walls','How does the abdominal thrust create enough pressure to expel a foreign object?',18),(175,'C','MEDIUM','Sitting upright in a chair','Lying flat on their back','Leaning forward with head lower than chest so the object can fall out','Standing fully upright and straight','What position should a choking person be in when receiving back blows?',18),(176,'A','EASY','Within 20 to 60 seconds','Only after 10 minutes','Within 5 minutes minimum','After 30 minutes','How quickly can drowning cause death?',19),(177,'B','EASY','They choose not to call for help','They are focused on keeping their mouth above water and cannot wave','They are unconscious already','They are too far away to be heard','Why do drowning people not shout for help?',19),(178,'C','EASY','Jump, Swim, Grab, Pull','Call, Shout, Wave, Dive','Reach, Throw, Row, Go','Run, Shout, Row, Swim','What is the correct order of water rescue methods?',19),(179,'D','EASY','The person is treading water safely','The person is diving for objects','The person is stretching in the water','A person is likely drowning and cannot stay horizontal','What does a vertical body position in water usually indicate?',19),(180,'B','EASY','Nothing ΓÇö enter the water immediately','Any floating object such as a life ring or rope','A heavy rope only','Your clothing only','What should you throw to a drowning person if you cannot reach them?',19),(181,'C','EASY','Whether they have swallowed water','Their pulse at the wrist','Responsiveness and normal breathing','Their eye response only','After rescuing a drowned person what is the first thing to check?',19),(182,'D','MEDIUM','Rescue breaths are easier to perform','Chest compressions cause vomiting when water is present','Water must be removed from lungs first','Drowning is a hypoxic arrest ΓÇö the heart stops due to lack of oxygen','Why do you start CPR for drowning with rescue breaths first?',19),(183,'A','MEDIUM','Delayed breathing difficulty from water in the lungs occurring hours later','A second drowning incident on the same day','Drowning in very shallow water','Drowning caused by a medical condition','What is secondary drowning?',19),(184,'B','MEDIUM','Only within one hour','Up to 24 hours','Only within 6 hours','Only immediately after rescue','How many hours after a water incident can secondary drowning occur?',19),(185,'D','MEDIUM','The water is too cold for untrained rescuers','There is no danger if you are a good swimmer','You may be arrested for interference','The drowning person may push you underwater in desperation','What is the danger of entering the water to rescue a drowning person without training?',19),(186,'B','MEDIUM','30 compressions then 2 breaths same as standard','2 rescue breaths then 30 chest compressions','5 breaths then 15 compressions','2 breaths only with no compressions needed','What is the CPR ratio for a drowning victim?',19),(187,'C','MEDIUM','Vomiting immediately after rescue','Skin discolouration only','Persistent coughing, chest pain, and extreme fatigue','Rapid heartbeat only','What is the main sign of secondary drowning to watch for after a water incident?',19),(188,'C','MEDIUM','Water drains naturally during compressions','Draining water is not physically possible','It wastes critical time when oxygen deprivation is causing brain damage','The water protects the lungs temporarily','Why should you not stop CPR to drain water from a drowning victim?',19),(189,'D','MEDIUM','The person is wearing contact lenses','The person is looking for something underwater','Normal relaxed swimming posture','The person is drowning and not in conscious control','What is a glassy or unfocused gaze in the water a sign of?',19),(190,'C','HARD','When they can walk and talk normally','When they stop coughing completely','Never ΓÇö all drowning victims must go to hospital due to secondary drowning risk','After 30 minutes of normal breathing','When is it safe to assume a recovered drowning victim needs no hospital care?',19),(191,'B','HARD','The person just finished exercising','Active drowning ΓÇö the person is in respiratory distress','The person is practising breathing techniques','The person is preparing to dive','What does hyperventilating or gasping at the water surface indicate?',19),(192,'D','HARD','Water freezes the lung tissue','Water adds weight that compresses the heart','Water dilutes the blood causing anaemia','Water causes inflammation and fluid buildup that prevents oxygen exchange','How does water in the lungs cause secondary drowning?',19),(193,'C','HARD','They have muscle cramps from cold water','They are unconscious already','The instinctive drowning response uses all body control to keep the airway above water','They are too exhausted to wave','What is the physiological reason drowning people cannot wave for help?',19),(194,'B','HARD','They are wearing a swimcap incorrectly','They have lost motor control ΓÇö a drowning sign','They are resting face down intentionally','They are performing a surface dive','What does hair over a drowning person face indicate?',19),(195,'D','HARD','At least waist depth','At least chest depth','Drowning only occurs when fully submerged','As little as a few centimetres ΓÇö even a face in a bowl of water','What depth of water is required for drowning to occur?',19),(196,'B','HARD','Suffocation','Aspiration','Embolism','Asphyxiation','What is the medical term for the condition when the airway fills with water?',19),(197,'C','HARD','Shivering generates heat to warm the heart','Cold water prevents brain damage','The mammalian dive reflex slows the heart and diverts blood to vital organs','Cold water hardens the arteries','In cold water drowning what physiological response actually helps survival?',19),(198,'C','HARD','The person is doing backstroke','The person is floating for rest','Passive drowning ΓÇö the person has likely lost consciousness','The person is waiting for a wave','What does the head tilted back with mouth open at water level indicate?',19),(199,'B','HARD','For 10 minutes maximum','Until the person is warm and dead ΓÇö not dead until warm and dead','Until the first shock from a defibrillator','Until the person vomits water','How long should CPR continue for a cold water drowning victim?',19),(200,'C','HARD','Fight them off and swim away immediately','Shout for help and stay above water','Take a breath, go underwater ΓÇö the person will release their grip to reach the surface','Dive under them and push them up','What is the recommended action if a drowning person grabs you and pulls you under?',19),(201,'A','EASY','Flash flood','River overflow flood','Coastal flood','Seasonal flood','What type of flood develops within six hours of heavy rainfall?',20),(202,'B','EASY','50 centimetres','15 centimetres','1 metre','Only waist-deep water','How much fast-moving water can knock a person off their feet?',20),(203,'C','EASY','Call family members first','Gather all valuables quickly','Move immediately to higher ground','Wait to see how bad it gets','What is the first action you should take during a flood?',20),(204,'D','EASY','1 metre depth only','30 centimetres','Only above roof level','60 centimetres','How much moving water can carry away a car?',20),(205,'B','EASY','Stay inside and call for help','Unlock doors and open the window immediately before water rises too high','Move to the back seat away from the engine','Wait for the water to stop rising','What should you do first if trapped in a flooding vehicle?',20),(206,'C','EASY','It is too cold to touch','It causes allergic reactions only','It contains sewage, chemicals, debris and live electrical current','It contains too much salt','Why is floodwater dangerous after a flood recedes?',20),(207,'D','MEDIUM','Drive quickly along the main road','Cross the nearest bridge to the other side','Follow the flood direction downstream','Move to high ground immediately usin